summary:
24. The Ivorian authorities must implement the action plan to enforce the Kimberley Process minimum requirements.

25. The Ivorian authorities are encouraged to participate in the OECD-hosted implementation programme.

26. The Ivorian authorities must dismantle illegal taxation networks and reduce checkpoints.

27. The Group of Experts must assess the effectiveness of border measures and control.

28. All States and organizations are urged to cooperate fully with the Committee, the Group of Experts, UNOCI, and French forces.
The Security Council:

 Reiterates its requests to the Group of Experts to coordinate with all political actors;

 Requests the Special Representatives of the Secretary-General for Children and Armed Conflict and for Sexual Violence in Conflict to share relevant information with the Committee;

 Urges Ivorian parties and States, particularly in the region, to ensure:

- Safety of the Group of Experts' members;
- Unhindered access to persons, documents, and sites for the Group to execute its mandate;

Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
